      <akn:section eId="sec_19_1304_02">
        <akn:num>19-1304.02</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Requirements for creation.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_19-1304_02_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A trust is created only if:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_19-1304_02_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A beneficiary is definite if the beneficiary can be ascertained now or in the future, subject to any applicable rule against perpetuities.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_19-1304_02_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A power in a trustee to select a beneficiary from an indefinite class is valid. If the power is not exercised within a reasonable time, the power fails and the property subject to the power passes to the persons who would have taken the property had the power not been conferred.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
